c: 3
v: 79
t: "It is not (possible) that a man, to whom is given the Book, and Wisdom, and the position of a prophet, can say to people; \"Be you my worshippers rather than Allah’s:\" On the contrary (he would say): \"Be you the worshippers of Him, Who is truly the Cherisher of all: For you have been taught the Book and you have studied it truthfully"